APPLY NOW: UH Maui Power Pathways Program (for Maui & Moloka'i residents) APPLY NOW: UH Maui Power Pathways Program (for Maui & Moloka'i residents) Kickstart Your Career with Hawaiian Electric This Spring!
Are you ready to explore the world of power generation? Join Hawaiian Electric’s Power Pathways program—an exciting, hands-on training opportunity designed to introduce you to the fundamentals of power plant operations.
Over the course of 10 weeks, you’ll gain real-world experience in various roles within the Generation Division at Hawaiian Electric, including:
Electrical systems
Combustion turbine operations
Instrumentation and control technology
Diesel mechanics
Plant operations
Eligibility Requirements:
Must be at least 18 years old
Maui or Molokaʻi resident
Drivers license eligible
Able to pass a criminal background check, drug test, and pre-employment screening
Don’t miss this chance to build valuable skills and explore a future in energy!

 Home About Contact FAQ Pricing Canine Cardio Hawaii 
 Where Health Meets Happiness Unleash your dog's energy! Get Started Introduction Canine Cardio Hawaii LLC is Hawaii's first and only veterinary professional owned mobile dog gym! We are a Kailua based, female owned and operated, dog-powered exercise service that provides an easy and safe alternative way to exercise your dog. I come to your home and provide a fulfilling and safe workout for your dog in my fully equipped and climate controlled trailer. I am here to help the dogs of Hawai'i live a happier, healthier, and longer life through regular exercise. Canine Cardio Hawaii is where health meets happiness! What is a mobile dog gym? 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 Temperature Controlled Our trailer is equipped with cold air conditioning to ensure that your dog can exercise comfortably, no matter the weather conditions outside. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 100% Pup-Powered Our treadmills (called slatmills) are specifically designed with dogs in mind. They are low resistance, low impact, and have no motor, so your dog can go as fast (or slow) as they want and even stop if they are tired. Safety is ensured by clipping the dogs harness to the slatmill so that they don't fall off and dogs are continuously monitored by our expert coach. 
 
 
 
 
 
 Convenient We come to you! This makes exercising your dog easier than ever. As long as there is a parking space

 A selection of my published pieces. 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 

 

 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 ICONIC STORYTELLERS Savvy 360 Oahu Spring/Summer This story delves into the creation of ʻAuana, the first Cirque du Soleil set in Hawaiʻi. From the costumery to the choreography, the creative team behind ʻAuana brings legends to life on this stage.  

 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 

 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 LEGENDARY TASTEMAKERS Savvy 360 Hawaii Spring/Summer This article highlights the exciting new venture that Richard Geoffrey has embarked upon. Following his retirement as the cellar master of Dom Perignon, he has reinvented himself as a major player in the world of sake. Pulling from his extensive experience in the world of champagne, he blends his old and new venture together in his new sake company, Iwa.  

 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 

 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 
 
 

 DESTINATION: HANAPĒPĒ Savvy 360 Destinations Join me on a walking tour of Hanapēpē, Kauaʻi's "Biggest Little Town." Once the bubbling epicenter of life on the island, Hanapēpē Town has reinvented itself time and time again providing to be "the town that refuses to die." Let's stroll this historic town and explore the southwestern part of Kauaʻi. #kauai #walkingtours #history

 International Assistance Dog Alliance Home About Us The Board Members Candidates Members Grievence Process Test Assistance Dog AKC Free Training Resources Contact Us Expanding Access. Elevating Standards. Welcome to the International Assistance Dog Alliance (IADA)!  

 ​ 

 What We Do 

 ​ 

 IADA is a professional, inclusive organization committed to setting and upholding high standards in the training, evaluation, and certification of assistance dogs and their handlers. Whether you’re a training organization, an independent trainer, or an owner-trainer, IADA exists to offer guidance, structure, and a supportive global community dedicated to the responsible development of assistance dog teams. 

 ​ 

 Accreditation 

 ​ 

 IADA’s accreditation process is designed to help the public identify ethical, trustworthy, and skilled assistance dog professionals. Accredited members demonstrate a commitment to humane training practices, the wellbeing of their dogs, and the creation of confident, capable teams. Our standards ensure that organizations and trainers are inclusive, ethical, and focused on excellence in both care and results. 

 ​ 

 Testing 

 ​ 

 In collaboration with Dauntless Companions, the founding training organization behind IADA, we offer free access to a variety of tests including AKC titles, in-training evaluations, public access testing, obedience, and trick dog tests. These tests are meant to support voluntary certification for assistance
